---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';

const faqs = [
	{
		q: 'Is my data sent anywhere?',
		a: "No. Your vault is a file on your device. Retrivo has no server, no account, and no telemetry that reads the contents of your vault - there's nothing centralized to breach, because nothing is centralized. The code is open source (MIT license) on GitHub, so you don't have to take our word for it - read the encryption code yourself, or see the full breakdown on the <a href=\"/security\" class=\"underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground\">Security page</a>."
	},
	{
		q: 'Does it work outside India?',
		a: "Yes. The core product - a hotkey vault for repeated details - is not India-specific. The built-in categories just happen to include common Indian fields (PAN, Aadhaar, GST, UPI, IFSC) because that's where the friction is worst. You can rename, remove, or add any fields you like, so a UK VAT number or a US SSN works just as well."
	},
	{
		q: 'What happens if I lose my computer?',
		a: "Because storage is local, we can't recover a vault we never had. Retrivo includes JSON export and import so you can keep your own encrypted backup wherever you want - a personal cloud drive, an external disk, a password manager attachment. Set a reminder to export regularly."
	},
	{
		q: 'What if I share this PC with someone else?',
		a: 'Turn on PIN lock in Settings → Security. It requires a PIN to open Retrivo, auto-locks after 15 minutes idle, and locks you out for a short cooldown after repeated wrong attempts. Off by default since not everyone needs it, but a one-click toggle if you do.'
	},
	{
		q: 'Which versions of Windows are supported?',
		a: "Windows 10 (build 1809) and later, on 64-bit processors. Windows 11 is fully supported. We don't currently support Windows 7, Windows 8, ARM64 devices, macOS, or Linux."
	},
	{
		q: 'How does the auto-paste work?',
		a: 'When a text field is focused, Retrivo copies the selected value and simulates a paste. In apps that block simulated paste, the value stays on the clipboard so you can paste it manually. Nothing about the destination app is logged.'
	},
	{
		q: 'Can I use Retrivo with a password manager?',
		a: 'Yes. Retrivo is meant for structured personal and financial details, not passwords. Keep passwords in a password manager and everything else - PAN, Aadhaar, bank details, addresses - in Retrivo.'
	}
];
---

<Layout title="FAQ" description="Straight answers about local storage, Windows support, auto-paste, and using Retrivo alongside a password manager.">
	<Hero eyebrow="FAQ" title="Straight answers." lead="If your question isn't here, the answer is probably in Features. If it isn't there either, email us." />

	<Section class="pb-24">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl divide-y divide-border overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-card">
			{
				faqs.map((item) => (
					<details class="group px-6 py-5 open:bg-surface/50">
						<summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4">
							<span class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">{item.q}</span>
							<svg
								viewBox="0 0 24 24"
								class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-subtle transition-transform group-open:rotate-45"
								fill="none"
								stroke="currentColor"
								stroke-width="2"
							>
								<path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke-linecap="round" />
							</svg>
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground" set:html={item.a} />
					</details>
				))
			}
		</div>
	</Section>
</Layout>
